    "department": "Engineering",
    "description": "Why Clarium?\n\nOur mission is to accelerate healthcare transformation through our AI-powered platform. We strive toward a future where hospitals are at the cutting edge of technology, operations and efficiency. Healthcare workers are inundated with endless tasks, manual processes and often unintuitive tools. Clarium is transforming healthcare by empowering providers with AI-powered software with intelligent workflow automation and actionable insights.\n\nWe envision a future where all hospitals leverage our collaborative data platform to automate their daily operational and administrative tasks, only surfacing high complexity issues that truly require their expertise.\n\nWe're backed by some of the biggest and most innovative investors in the world including: Northzone, General Catalyst, AlleyCorp, 1984 Ventures, Alumni Ventures, and others.\n\nRole Overview\n\nWe’re looking for a Senior Fullstack Engineer that’s passionate about using their skills to unlock efficiency for hospitals and their suppliers. In this role, you’ll work to design, build, and maintain end-to-end features within our platform. You’ll work with a fast-paced, cross-functional team, to deliver end-user facing features quickly and iterate based on customer feedback.\n\nThe role is ideal for someone who enjoys owning features from concept to production and is comfortable working across our frontend (React/Typescript) and backend (Python/FastAPI) codebases.\n\nResponsibilities\n\n - Write high-quality, well-tested, maintainable code\n\n - Design, build, and maintain backend APIs and frontend components for end-user facing features\n\n - Collaborate with internal product managers and customers to align product development with real-world needs\n\nRequirements\n\n - 5+ years of relevant industry experience\n\n - Strong experience with Python\n\n - Strong experience designing and consuming RESTful APIs\n\n - Strong experience with React and Typescript\n\n - Experience with SQL\n\n - Self-motivated with excellent problem-solving and communication skills\n\nNice-to-Haves\n\n - Experience with FastAPI\n\n - Experience working in healthtech\n\n - Experience working at a startup",
